UNITED STATES ex rel. Melchiore SPATARO, Relator-Appellant, v. Benjamin M. DAY, Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of New York, Respondent-Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 20, 1928. No. 210. Charles E. Healy, of New York City, for appellant. Charles H. Tuttle, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Abbot Low Moffat, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order is affirmed, on the authority of Chung v. Nagle (C. C. A.) 15 F.(2d) 789, and United States ex rel. Grimaldi v. Ebey (C. C. A.) 12 F.(2d) 922.
